</tbody></table></td></tr>
</tbody></table>

<p id="mwBNs">When counted, nouns take one of a small set of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Measure_word" title="Measure word" id="mwBNw">measure words</a>. Similar to Japanese, the nouns in Bengali cannot be counted by adding the numeral directly adjacent to the noun. The noun's measure word (<b id="mwBN0">MW</b>) must be used between the numeral and the noun. Most nouns take the generic measure word <span lang="bn" title="Bengali language text" about="#mwt526" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"lang","href":"./Template:Lang"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"bn"},"2":{"wt":"-টা"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBN4">-টা</span><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Bengali-language_text" about="#mwt526" id="mwBN8"/> <i id="mwBOA">-ṭa</i>, though other measure words indicate semantic classes (e.g. <span lang="bn" title="Bengali language text" about="#mwt527" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"lang","href":"./Template:Lang"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"bn"},"2":{"wt":"-জন"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBOE">-জন</span><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Bengali-language_text" about="#mwt527" id="mwBOI"/> <i id="mwBOM">-jôn</i> for humans). There is also the classifier <i id="mwBOQ">-khana,</i> and its diminutive form <i id="mwBOU">-khani</i>, which only attach to nouns which are flat, long, square, or thin. These are the least common of the classifiers.<sup about="#mwt1022" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-78" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-78"}}'><a href="./Bengali_language#cite_note-78" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 78;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[78]</span></a></sup></p>

